The paper deals with the problem of classifying ECG signals for predicting the onset of Paroxysmal Atrial Fibrillation (PAF). The proposed method involves feature extraction and classification based on kernel similarities for multi-variate time series. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to the development of algorithms and models for classification and prediction tasks. Additionally, the paper deals with a biomedical application, which could place it in the cs.BIO (Computational Biology) sub-category. Finally, the use of time series data and kernel methods could also suggest the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, which deals with the analysis of complex data structures.
